9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to education; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 11-103.6a-1, which relates to legislative
11 review of subject matter standards; disapproving
submitted standards when the Legislature fails to
12 adopt a joint resolution; and providing an effective
date.
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 11-103.6a-1,
18 is amended to read as follows:
19 Section 11-103.6a-1. A. All subject matter standards and
20 revisions to the standards adopted by the State Board of Education
21 pursuant to Section 11-103.6a of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes
22 shall be subject to legislative review as set forth in this section.
23 The standards shall not be implemented by the State Board of
24
HB2987 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Educ ation until the legislative review process is completed as
2 provided for in this section.
3 B. Upon adoption of any subject matter standards, the State
4 Board of Education shall submit the adopted standards to the Speaker
5 of the House of Representatives or a designee and the President Pro
6 Tempore of the Senate or a designee prior to the last thirty (30)
7 days of the legislative session.
8 C. By adoption of a joint resolution, the Legislature shall
9 approve the standards, disapprove the standards in whole or in part,
10 amend the standards in whole or in part or disapprove the standards
11 in whole or in part with instructions to the State Board of
12 Education, provided that such joint resolution becomes law in
13 accordance with Section 11 of Article VI of the Oklahoma
14 Constitution. If the joint resolution is vetoed by the Governor in
15 accordance with Section 11 of Article VI of the Oklahoma
16 Constitution and the veto has not been overridden, the standards
17 shall be deemed approved. If the Legislature fails to adopt a joint
18 resolution within thirty (30) legislative days following submission
19 of the standards, the standards shall be deemed approved
20 disapproved.
21 D. If the subject matter standards are disapproved in whole or
22 are disapproved in whole with instructions as provided for in this
23 section, the State Board of Education may adopt new standards and
24 submit the new standards for legislative review pursuant to this
HB2987 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 sect ion. The State Board of Education shall continue to implement
2 current standards in place until the new standards have been
3 reviewed by the Legislature and approved as provided for in this
4 section. If the subject matter standards are amended, approved in
5 part or are disapproved in part with instructions, the State Board
6 of Education may revise the standards in accordance with the
7 legislative changes and implement the standards.
8 E. Upon final approval of the standards, the standards shall be
9 considered final agency rules. The Board shall submit a copy of the
10 standards to the Secretary of State, who shall include the standards
11 in the publication known as the "Oklahoma Administrative Code" in
12 the same manner as agency rules are published in the "Code" as
13 provided for in the Administrative Procedures Act. All standards
14 approved and published as provided for in this subsection shall have
15 the same force and effect of law as agency rules promulgated
16 pursuant to the Administrative Procedures Act.
17 F. Unless otherwise provided by specific vote of the
18 Legislature, joint resolutions introduced for purposes of approving,
19 disapproving, amending or disapproving with instructions any subject
20 matter standards shall not be subject to regular legislative cutoff
21 dates, shall be limited to such provisions as may be necessary for
22 approving, disapproving, amending or disapproving with instructions
23 any subject matter standards and any such other direction or mandate
24
HB2987 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 rega rding the standards deemed necessary by the Legislature. The
2 joint resolution shall contain no other provisions.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
